en  , or of any other Scandinavian or North German patronymic from a personal name derived from Old Norse <i>Eiríkr</i>, which is composed of <i>ei</i> ‘ever, always’ (or a shortened form of <i>ein</i> ‘one, only’) + <i>rík</i> ‘power’. Compare   Ericksen  ,   Ericson  , and   Erikson  .","English (Lancashire): patronymic from the Middle English male personal name <i>Eric</i> (with the same etymology as 1 above) + <i>son</i>."]},{"name":"Erekson","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Thor.","Americanized form of Swedish   Eriksson   or of any other Scandinavian patronymic from a personal name derived from Old Norse <i>Eiríkr</i> (see   Erickson  )."]},{"name":"Ericsson","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Lars, Sven, Anders, Britt, Gunvor, Johan, Kerstin, Tor.","Swedish: variant of   Eriksson  . Compare   Erickson   and   Ericson  ."]}]},{"name":"Ekeblad","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Swedish: ornamental name composed of the elements <i>ek</i> ‘oak’ +<i>blad</i> ‘leaf’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Anders","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Vernacular form of   Andreas ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1702076,"age":36,"year":"1436","julianDay":2245548,"title":"The Engelbrekt Rebellion","description":"Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson, a Swedish mine owner and statesman, led a rebellion against Eric of Pomerania, King of the Kalmar Union. Sweden was upset with the Danes' interference with Swedish exports and unjust collection of taxes. The Engelbrekt Rebellion led to the deposing of Eric of Pomerania and the eventual dissolution of the Kalmar Union.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1357051,"age":95,"year":"1495","julianDay":2267098,"description":"Russians forces invade Sweden.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1702078,"age":95,"year":"1495","toYear":"1497","julianDa